This paper deals with transfer learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on measuring transferability for datasets with different feature spaces and distributions, which suggests that it could also fall under the sub-categories of "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) and "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of classifiers and discriminators, which are common tools in natural language processing (NLP) and could place it under the sub-category of "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the use of feature transformation layers and a mean distance loss, which are also common in neural networks and could place it under the sub-category of "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
